  I think you would have at least over one hundred 55+ wizards.  Probably a good number more than that.  At peak time the number of 60th level wizards is well into double figures alone, so i think my estimate is conservative to say the least.<br>
  For example, let us say you have one hundred wizards between levels fifty-two and sixty.  Every one of those wizards can cast a lure.  That's 640 points of damage each.  Lol, unless you get lots of resists. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Even assuming a fifty percent resist rate you could, in theory, do 32,000 points of damage every time your combined force casts.  With that kind of damage output even the mobs with 100,000+ hit points wouldn't take that long to kill.  To help ensure your wizards survived to cast their spells you could have a couple of normal groups to act as a distraction.  That coupled with the manaskins and shields cast before the fight began should be enough to ensure a victory.<br>
  You would have to do some test runs.  Say with the two &quot;normal&quot; groups and two or three wizard ones of the level range i mentioned, fifty-two to sixty.  Then you could take logs of the fights.  See how much damage your wizards do.  How long they can survive.  The resist rate for the different levels.  From all of that, it would then be possible to plan more effectively how to take the full raiding force into the fight.<br>
  At the moment i feel that wizards are playing EQ in a style suits melee.  Why?  The long drawn out fight isn't what a wizard is good at.  So why are we allowing things to be like this.  Part of it is that strategies have been formed that people know work and another part is that you enjoy playing with people of mixed classes.  However, the current raiding style isn't, in my opinion, good for wizards.  It is not how we fight.  The fast burn is our style, not the long fight.<br>
  Would people care to try this kind of thing?<br>
<br>
Talinath.<br>
