  As a side point, it would be fun clearing the way to the &quot;big&quot; mobs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Just think of it.  Assists wouldn't be that big of thing if you were in a zone that had lots of named mobs like Kael.  With groups made entirely of wizards, all you would need to do was ensure that everyone knew their group number.  Then it would just be a case of calling the name of the mob and the groups that are to blast it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Lol, pulling?  What's that? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  You could use leapfrog tactics to advance.  First two groups kill mob A.  They sit down to med.  The other fifteen groups move on.  Groups three and four blast mob B.  They sit down to med.  The other thirteen groups move on to the next area.  Four mobs here.  Groups five and six on mob C.  Seven and eight on mob D.  Nine and ten on mob E.  Eleven and twelve on mob F.  Force moves on.  Groups one and two have regained their mana and have caught up again.  And so on.<br>
  With that kind of firepower in one place, each wizard would likely only be casting the once, so it wouldn't take very long for them to get their mana back.  So you could clear your way through a zone at a great speed. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  One argument about such a force/guild would be that it never offered much to the wizards involved or the or classes supporting it.  I disagree. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Getting a armour drop for the dwarf quests in Kael would be slow.  With one hundred plus wizards in the force/guild there would be a long list.  However, if you cleared it from top to bottom on a regular basis, how long would it take to get the armour drops?  It wouldn't happen overnight, but within what i would term as a reasonable amount of time the majority of you force/guild would be equipped with the dwarf quest armour.  Lol, or dragon quest armour if you are doing ToV. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  For the non-cloth classes things would be amazing in such a force/guild.  True, you would not be performing in your traditional/accepted fashion, but you would still be a much needed person.  There is also the fact that since there wouldn't be that many plate/chain classes in the force/guild the competition for those armour drops would low to say the least.  So the melee/wis classes would be equipped with dwarf or dragon armour pretty quickly, which is all to the good.<br>
  The melee style is not our style.  We have played in a way that suits melee for a long time.  It doesn't have to be like this.  If we really want to we can play in a way which suits our class.  All we need is the courage and belief in ourselves to step outside the &quot;accepted&quot; way of doing things.  Take some chances.  Experiment.  I feel that the combined force of wizards could do almost anything within EQ if we would just work together and give it a try.<br>
  Would anyone else like to give it a try?<br>
<br>
