  The way i am looking at the Conclave of Wizards is that we wouldn't be a guild.  Lol, or not at first anyway. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Instead we would be a loose organisation of like minded individuals, i.e. wizards, who would gather on say a Friday and Saturday night to cause some havoc in a few zones. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  The reason for such a loose organisation is that people are in guilds that they like and you don't want to put them on a spot by demanding their loyalty.  Not only is it unlikely to work, it is totally unnecessary.  With a loose organisation of wizards, you would only really come together on those few days, or more often if people felt like it, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  so people could still maintain presence within their old guild.<br>
  So on a Friday or/and a Saturday night we all gather in Greater Fay.  Lol, or West Common. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We then do a quick check to find out what is available.  With people from so many different guilds, it should be a pretty simple thing to find out pretty quickly what is camped and what isn't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We would then up sticks and go toward our intended destination.  Within a short period of time we should be there.  Then it would be a case of burning the zone to the ground. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Lol, or to &quot;borrow&quot; an old quote, &quot;Kill them all.  Let god sort them out.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  Think of it like this.  &quot;Tradional&quot; tactics have &quot;epic&quot; fights lasting for things like fifteen minutes to half an hour.  Once the Conclave of Wizards had their tactics all worked out, it would take us between thirty seconds and a minute to kill those same mobs.  Lol, at a guess. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You also have the fact that prep time would be very short.  You could make it longer to get buffs from other classes, but since the majority of the raiding force would be wizards that is really a moot point.<br>
  In effect what a raiding force made up mostly of wizards would be is a lot like a fast reaction force.  We don't need a lot of time to get to a location.  We don't need a lot of time buffing.  With the leapfrop tactics we wouldn't take long to get into position for the attack on the boss mob.  Lastly, with the leapfrog tactics the raiding force should arrive in a condition both physically and magically to be attack near enough instantly.<br>
  The more i think about the idea.  The more i like it.  It might take a few attempts to perfect, but once it is, i think (hope) it would be almost unstoppable. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  Hmm.  I was thinking.  Is it time to raise the banner for the formation of the Conclave of Wizards on the main discussion board?  Lol, might get more people to visit us here in the wilderness. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
